        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:01PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Washburn, or 10 miles southwest of Panhandle,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Panhandle, Washburn, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
